LEGISLATURE OF NEBRASKA
ONE HUNDRED NINTH LEGISLATURE
SECOND SESSION
LEGISLATIVE BILL 1243
Introduced by Murman, 38; Clements, 2; Holdcroft, 36; Lippincott, 34.
Read first time January 21, 2026
Committee: Education
1 A BILL FOR AN ACT relating to education; to amend section 79-2,136,
2 Revised Statutes Supplement, 2025; to change provisions relating to
3 part-time enrollment; and to repeal the original section.
4 Be it enacted by the people of the State of Nebraska,
-1-

LB1243 LB1243
2026 2026
1 Section 1. Section 79-2,136, Revised Statutes Supplement, 2025, is
2 amended to read:
3 79-2,136 (1) Each school board shall allow the part-time enrollment
4 of students, for all courses selected by the students, who are residents
5 of, or admitted to, the school district pursuant to subsection (1), (2),
6 or (11) of section 79-215 and who are also enrolled in a private,
7 denominational, or parochial school or in a school which elects pursuant
8 to section 79-1601 not to meet accreditation or approval requirements and
9 shall establish policies and procedures for such part-time enrollment.
10 Such policies and procedures may include provisions permitting the part-
11 time enrollment of such students who are not residents of, or admitted
12 to, such school districts to the extent permitted pursuant to section
13 79-215 and may require part-time students to follow school policies that
14 apply to other students at any time the part-time student is present on
15 school grounds or at a school-sponsored activity or athletic event. Part-
16 time enrollment shall not entitle a student to transportation or
17 transportation reimbursements pursuant to section 79-611.
18 (2) Each school board shall establish policies and procedures to
19 allow any student who is a resident of, or admitted to, the school
20 district pursuant to subsection (1), (2), or (11) of section 79-215 and
21 who is enrolled in a school which elects pursuant to section 79-1601 not
22 to meet accreditation or approval requirements to participate in any
23 extracurricular activities as defined in section 79-2,126, including, but
24 not limited to, interschool competitions, to the same extent and subject
25 to the same requirements, conditions, and procedures as a student
26 enrolled in a public school governed by such board, except that any
27 school which elects pursuant to section 79-1601 not to meet accreditation
28 or approval requirements shall set the standards for satisfactory
29 academic performance for a student from the school to participate in
30 extracurricular activities pursuant to this subsection and shall provide
31 assurances of compliance with such academic standards.
-2-

