1 (3) School board policies and procedures adopted pursuant to
2 subsection (2) of this section:
3 (a) Shall shall require any student desiring to participate in
4 extracurricular activities regulated by an athletics or activities
5 association to which such school is a member pursuant to such subsection
6 to be enrolled in five credit hours offered by the school district in any
7 semester in order to participate in such extracurricular activities, but
8 may not prohibit a student from enrolling in more than five credit
9 hours; ,
10 (b) Shall not require any student desiring to participate in an
11 extracurricular activity that is not regulated by an athletics or
12 activities association to be enrolled in any minimum number of credit
13 hours offered by the school district in order to participate in such
14 extracurricular activity;
15 (c) Shall shall not allow any preference in the selection of a
16 student for participation in an extracurricular activity based on such
17 student's status as a full-time student in the school district; , and
18 (d) May (c) may require any student participating in extracurricular
19 activities pursuant to such subsection to follow school policies that
20 apply to other students when present on school grounds or at a school-
21 sponsored activity or athletic event.
22 (4) Participation in extracurricular activities pursuant to
23 subsection (2) of this section shall not entitle a student to
24 transportation, except to and from practices and events to the same
25 extent as public school students participating in such activities, or
26 transportation reimbursement pursuant to section 79-611.
27 (5) (4) Nothing in this section shall be construed to exempt any
28 student from the compulsory attendance provisions of section 79-201 or
29 any statutes relating to habitual truancy.
30 Sec. 2. Original section 79-2,136, Revised Statutes Supplement,
31 2025, is repealed.
